---
import Newspaper from "@/layouts/Newspaper.astro";

export const prerender = false;

const EFFECTIVE = "May 18, 2026";
---

<Newspaper title="Terms of service — Lighthouse" section="LEGAL"
           pageHeading="Terms of service"
           pageSubhead={`Effective ${EFFECTIVE}.`}>
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto chunk-prose">
    <p>
      These terms govern your use of Lighthouse at lighthouse.harborgang.com
      and the MCP endpoint at <code>/mcp/</code> ("the Service"). The Service
      is operated by Harbor Gang ("we", "us"). By creating an account or
      using the Service you agree to these terms.
    </p>

    <h2>The Service</h2>
    <p>
      Lighthouse is a retrieval engine over canonical SDLC reference content —
      RFCs, OWASP, NIST SP-800, framework documentation, practitioner
      writing, and post-cutoff release streams. It exposes a search API
      consumable over HTTP and Model Context Protocol. The corpus is
      assembled from public sources; we make a best effort to keep it
      current and accurate but make no warranty as to completeness or
      correctness.
    </p>

    <h2>Accounts</h2>
    <p>
      You may use Lighthouse anonymously within the anonymous-tier daily
      limit. Higher tiers require an account, created by signing in with an
      identity provider through Auth0. You're responsible for activity under
      your account; keep your credentials confidential.
    </p>

    <h2>Subscriptions and payment</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Paddle.com Market Limited is the Merchant of Record for paid
        subscriptions. Paddle's terms and refund policy apply to the
        transaction; Paddle handles VAT and other applicable taxes.
      </li>
      <li>
        Subscriptions renew automatically until cancelled. Cancel any time
        from your account; access continues until the end of the paid
        period.
      </li>
      <li>
        We may change prices for new subscriptions. Existing subscribers
        will receive at least 30 days notice before a renewal at a higher
        price.
      </li>
      <li>
        Refunds outside Paddle's standard policy are at our discretion —
        write to <a href="mailto:hello@harborgang.com">hello@harborgang.com</a>{" "}
        if you have a reason.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Respect the daily search caps for your tier. Automated mass-scraping
        of the corpus, or attempts to circumvent caps, are not permitted.
      </li>
      <li>
        Don't use the Service to do anything illegal, to harass anyone, or
        to attack other systems.
      </li>
      <li>
        Don't share MCP tokens publicly. Tokens are tied to your account and
        we treat misuse as your responsibility.
      </li>
      <li>
        We may rate-limit, suspend, or terminate accounts that violate
        these rules. For abuse that affects service stability we may act
        without prior notice.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Content and intellectual property</h2>
    <p>
      The ingested corpus consists of public material under its original
      licences. We surface excerpts with attribution to the original source;
      we don't claim ownership over the underlying content. The selection,
      curation, summaries, keywords, and ranking model are our own work —
      © {new Date().getFullYear()} Harbor Gang. The "Lighthouse" and
      "Harbor Gang" word marks belong to Harbor Gang.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranty; limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      The Service is provided "as is", without warranty of any kind. We take
      care with what we publish but cannot guarantee that every result is
      accurate, current, or fit for a particular purpose — including any
      use to ground LLM responses. To the maximum extent permitted by law,
      our aggregate liability for any claim arising out of these terms is
      capped at the amount you paid us for the Service in the 12 months
      before the claim.
    </p>

    <h2>Service availability</h2>
    <p>
      We aim for high availability but do not commit to a specific uptime
      SLA on the public tiers. Scheduled maintenance and unplanned
      incidents will sometimes interrupt the Service.
    </p>

    <h2>Termination</h2>
    <p>
      You can delete your account at any time by emailing us. We may
      terminate or suspend access for material breach of these terms,
      non-payment, or as required by law. On termination we'll delete or
      anonymise your data per the timelines in our{" "}
      <a href="/legal/privacy">privacy policy</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws of Ukraine, without regard to
      conflict-of-laws principles. Any dispute that cannot be resolved
      amicably will be submitted to the competent courts at our place of
      establishment. Mandatory consumer-protection rights under your local
      law are not affected.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      We may update these terms. Material changes will be posted here with
      an updated effective date and emailed to signed-in users at least 30
      days before they take effect.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions: <a href="mailto:hello@harborgang.com">hello@harborgang.com</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</Newspaper>
